Field Label: What is your biological sex (sex assigned at birth)?
Choices, Calculations, OR Slider Labels: 1, Male | 2, Female

Field Label: Are you pregnant or do you suspect you may be pregnant?
What is your current height?
What is your current weight (lb)?

Section Header: This section will ask you about you running background.
Field Label:
How many years have you been running regularly?

By "regularly," we mean you have typically run at least once per week, for about 1 mile (1.6 km) or more per run, on average. This includes normal breaks (for example, taking a week or two off after a race, illness, or vacation), as long as you returned to your usual running routine afterward.
Choices, Calculations, OR Slider Labels: 0, I have not been running regularly | 1, Less than a year | 2, 1-3 years | 3, 4-6 years | 4, 7-10 years | 5, 11-15 years | 6, More than 15 years

Field Label: How important is running to you compared with your other daily activities?
Choices, Calculations, OR Slider Labels: 1, Not important at all | 2, A little important | 3, Moderately important | 4, Very important | 5, The most important activity in my life

Field Label: Which of the following best describes how you see yourself as a runner currently?
Choices, Calculations, OR Slider Labels: 1, Fitness runner (I run mainly for health, fitness and enjoyment, but never do any competition) | 2, Recreational runner (I run mainly for fitness and enjoyment, and I sometimes enter community races (e.g., 5K, 10K, fun runs) but without structured training or competitive goals) | 3, Competitive runner (I train and race to improve performance, but not at an elite level) | 4, Elite runner (I train and compete at a very high or professional level)

Field Label: Which of the following best describes your competitive focus currently?
Choices, Calculations, OR Slider Labels: 1, Very short races (< 3.1 miles, < 5K) | 2, Short races (5-10K) | 3, Middle-distance races (half marathon) | 4, Marathon | 5, Ultra-distance races (>26.2 miles)

Section Header:
This section will ask you about your recent race performances over the past 12 months.

 

Note: If your running analysis took place during a race and that race prompted you to join the Sanford Stride Project, DO NOT list that race here. List the race before that.
Field Label: Over the past 12 months, what was the distance of your most recent race?
Choices, Calculations, OR Slider Labels: 0, I have not done a race in the past 12 months | 1, 5K | 2, 10K | 3, Half Marathon | 4, Marathon | 5, Other

Field Label: If other, please specify the distance (miles).

What was your finishing time (HH:MM:SS)?

Example: You did a 5K in 21 minutes and 30 seconds. Enter 00:21:30.

Section Header: This section will ask you about your training habits over the past 3 months.
Field Label: Over the past 3 months, did you follow a formal training plan (coach, online plan, structured program)?

Over the past 3 months, what has been your average weekly running milage (total milage for the week, on average)?

Example: If you run 3 miles 3 times per week, on average, your average weekly running milage is 9 miles.
Over the past 3 months, did your average weekly running mileage change significantly compared to the 3 months before that?
Choices, Calculations, OR Slider Labels: 1, Decreased over the last 3 months compared to the 3 months before that by more than 20% | 2, Decreased over the last 3 months compared to the 3 months before that (by less than 20%) | 3, No change over the last 3 months compared to the 3 months before that | 4, Increased over the last 3 months compared to the 3 months before that (by less than 20%) | 5, Increased over the last 3 months compared to the 3 months before that by more than 20%

Field Label: Over the past 3 months, how many days per week did you run, on average?
Choices, Calculations, OR Slider Labels: 1, 1 day | 2, 2 days | 3, 3 days | 4, 4 days | 5, 5 days | 6, 6 days | 7, 7 days

Field Label: Over the past 3 months, which of the following types of runs have you regularly included in your training? (check all that apply)
Choices, Calculations, OR Slider Labels: 1, Recovery (very easy runs to help your body recover) | 2, Easy / Long (easy runs or long slow runs to build endurance) | 3, Steady (runs at a steady, moderate pace) | 4, Tempo (comfortably hard runs you can hold for a while) | 5, Intervals (hard efforts for a few minutes, like track repeats or fartlek) | 6, Sprints (very hard efforts up to 30 seconds, like short sprints or hills)

Field Label:
Over the past 3 months, what was your typical training pace for your usual training runs?

By typical trainng pace, we mean the pace you most often run when you just head out for a normal run - not especially slow, not a race effort - but a steady, moderate pace.

Over the past 3 months, did the intensity of your training change compared to the 3 months before that?

By intensity, we mean how often you included tempo, interval, or sprint workouts, or how fast your typical training pace was for your usual training runs.
Choices, Calculations, OR Slider Labels: 1, Decreased over the past 3 months compared to the 3 months before that | 2, No change over the past 3 months compared to the 3 months before that | 3, Increased over the past 3 months compared to the 3 months before that

Section Header: The section will ask you about your cross training, strength, and flexibility training over the past 3 months.
Field Label: Over the past 3 months, have you regularly done in any of the following aerobic/endurance activities, in addition to running, at least once per week for 20 minutes or more? (check all that apply)
Choices, Calculations, OR Slider Labels: 1, Cycling (outdoor or stationary bike) | 2, Swimming | 3, Walking or hiking | 4, Elliptical | 5, Rowing

Field Label: Over the past 3 months, have you regularly done any of the following activities, in addition to running, at least once per week for 20 minutes or more? (check all that apply)
Choices, Calculations, OR Slider Labels: 1, Strength training (weights, resistance bands, bodyweight strength) | 2, Core stability or conditioning exercises (e.g., crunches, planks) | 3, Plyometric or jump training | 4, Stretching or mobility work (e.g., static or dynamic stretching, yoga, foam rolling)

Section Header: This section will ask you about any injuries you have had over the past 12 months.
Field Label: Over the past 12 months, have you had any lower-body problems, such as aches, pain, stiffness, swelling, or joint issues (like giving out or clicking), that made running harder or less comfortable?
Over the past 12 months, how much did lower-body problems affect your ability to participate in running?
Choices, Calculations, OR Slider Labels: 1, Full participation without problems | 2, Full participation, but with problems | 3, Reduced participation due to problems | 4, Could not participate due to problems

Field Label: Over the past 12 months, to what extent did you have to modify your training because of lower-body problems?
Choices, Calculations, OR Slider Labels: 1, No modification | 2, To a minor extent | 3, To a moderate extent | 4, To a major extent

Field Label: Over the past 12 months, to what extent did lower-body problems affect your running performance?
Choices, Calculations, OR Slider Labels: 1, No effect | 2, To a minor extent | 3, To a moderate extent | 4, To a major extent

Field Label: Over the past 12 months, to what extent did you experience pain in your lower-body while running?
Choices, Calculations, OR Slider Labels: 1, No pain | 2, Mild pain | 3, Moderate pain | 4, Severe pain

Field Label:
Over the past 12 months, how much did lower-body problems affect your running?

Please use a 0-10 scale, where 0 = no impact at all and 10 = completely prevented me from running.
Choices, Calculations, OR Slider Labels: No impact at all | Moderate impact | Completely prevent me from running

Field Label: Over the past 12 months, about how much total time did you have to reduce or completely stop running because of lower-body problems?
Choices, Calculations, OR Slider Labels: 1, I did not reduce or stop running | 2, Less than 7 days (less than a week) | 3, 7 to 13 days (1-2 weeks) | 4, 14 to 28 days (2-4 weeks) | 5, More than 28 days (over a month)

Field Label: Over the past 12 months, did you see a healthcare professional for your lower-body problems?
Choices, Calculations, OR Slider Labels: 1, No | 2, Yes, once | 3, Yes, more than once

Field Label: Over the past 12 months, which body parts on your RIGHT side have experienced a problem (pain, ache, stiffness, swelling, instability, giving way, locking/clicking) that affected your running? (check all that apply)
Choices, Calculations, OR Slider Labels: 1, Hip/groin | 2, Thigh/hamstring | 3, Knee | 4, Lower leg/shin (including calf) | 5, Achilles tendon | 6, Ankle | 7, Foot/toes | 8, Other

Field Label: Over the past 12 months, which body parts on your LEFT side have experienced a problem (pain, ache, stiffness, swelling, instability, giving way, locking/clicking) that affected your running? (check all that apply)
Choices, Calculations, OR Slider Labels: 1, Hip/groin | 2, Thigh/hamstring | 3, Knee | 4, Lower leg/shin (including calf) | 5, Achilles tendon | 6, Ankle | 7, Foot/toes | 8, Other
